    "body": "## Background\r\n\r\nThe app is able to show features and deprecations by reading Markdown files in the `source` directory. When a new version of Ember is released (for example, version 3.21), we need to generate Markdown files and provide relevant information.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nCurrently, the app doesn't show features and deprecations that were added to Ember.js, Ember Data, and Ember CLI in version 3.21.\r\n\r\n- https://upgrade-guide.netlify.app/?fromVersion=3.20\r\n\r\n\r\n## TODOs\r\n\r\n- [ ] Use Ember CLI to generate skeleton Markdown files for Ember.js, Ember Data, and Ember CLI.\r\n\r\n- [ ] List features and deprecations (if they exist) for Ember.js.\r\n\r\n- [ ] List features and deprecations (if they exist) for Ember Data.\r\n\r\n- [ ] List features and deprecations (if they exist) for Ember CLI.\r\n\r\n- [ ] Run the app locally to check that we can see features and deprecations when we select `3.21` for `To version`.\r\n\r\n\r\n## References\r\n\r\n- [Ember Blog - 3.21 Release](https://blog.emberjs.com/2020/09/02/ember-3-21-released.html)\r\n- [README - Code Generators](https://github.com/ember-learn/upgrade-guide/blob/45794a45e6676e7598f12e4b47a6cdd151b17149/README.md#adding-the-latest-ember-version)",
