    "body": "## Current Behaviour\r\n\r\nThe [Input Helper Section](https://guides.emberjs.com/v3.4.0/templates/input-helpers/) on the Guides highlights how different types of the `input` helper can be used.\r\nWhen reviewing the section on how to bind actions to the `{{input}}` helper (https://guides.emberjs.com/v3.4.0/templates/input-helpers/#toc_actions), the following statement is made:\r\n\r\n```Event Names must be dasherized.```\r\n\r\n<img width=\"805\" alt=\"capture d ecran 2018-10-03 a 00 22 42\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8811742/46380494-c19b9280-c6a2-11e8-9ca5-6238d5021505.png\">\r\n\r\nThis is in fact only true for the `{{input}}` helper with the `type=\"text\"`. This input helper requires the dasherized event name to be used to attach any actions:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{{input type=\"text\" focus-in=(action \"highlightUser\")}}\r\n```\r\n\r\nOther types of input helpers which do not rely on the `TextSupport` Mixin do not own any dasherized event name API and actions can only be attached to their respective event handlers via the camelizedSyntax (e.g. `focusIn`). An example for a kind of input helper which does not own any functionality of the `TextSupport` Mixin is the one with `type=\"checkbox\"`. For this, you can only attach actions as follows:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{{input type=\"checkbox\" focusIn=(action \"highlightUser\")}}\r\n```\r\n\r\nPlease also review [this stellar outline of the differences between both these uses in this issue](https://github.com/emberjs/ember.js/issues/16171).\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nThe section describing actions used with the `{{input}}` helper should explicitly describe which type of input helper will require which type of event name wording (dasherized vs. camelized). Preferrably, this section should highlight a table of all input helper types available and their corresponding event name style.\r\n\r\nPlease find out which input helpers / text area helpers are based on the [`TextSupport` mixin](https://github.com/emberjs/ember.js/blob/master/packages/@ember/-internals/views/lib/mixins/text_support.js) and list those together with the dasherized version of viable event names. All other input / text helper types should be listed together with the camelized version of the viable event names.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\nPlease update the Guides Source not only for the latest release `3.4`, but for any other preceding versions which include the statement about dasherized event names.\r\n\r\n## Sources\r\n- Guides Section on Actions Used With the Input Helper: https://guides.emberjs.com/v2.18.0/templates/input-helpers/#toc_actions\r\n- Original Issue about Discrepancy between `{{input type=\"text}}` and `{{input type=\"checkbox\"}}` regarding action binding: https://github.com/emberjs/ember.js/issues/16171\r\n- Ember Twiddle Demo from the Original Issue: https://ember-twiddle.com/6f82aa1cce20e0831e285c172ca7e998\r\n- Documentation on the Text Support Mixin: https://www.emberjs.com/api/ember/release/classes/Ember.TextSupport\r\n\r\n\r\n",
