    "closed_at": null,
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "active_lock_reason": null,
    "body": "When we released Octane, the API docs changed a whole bunch! Ideal Guides UX is that if someone is on an older version of Ember, like 3.12, if they follow the links to the API docs, they should see 3.12 docs (non-Octane). However, right now, a lot of links point directly to `api.emberjs.com/ember/release` and `api.emberjs.com/ember-data/release`.\r\n\r\nTo close this ticket, do a find-replace to change the \"release\" links to point to the appropriate version, for each version of the guides. The lastest version of the guides should still point to `release`, so don't change those.",
