    "body": "As of PR #637, we made the Ember API landing page show up on Ember Data too. But really, both Ember and Ember Data deserve their own landing pages!\r\n\r\nTo do:\r\n- Following the same pattern as #637, create a new page that has a list of commonly-searched-for documentation for Ember Data. Use your instincts about what to include - likely models, serializers, and adapters.\r\n- See the PR #637 for where to make the routing changes so that users see it when they visit `release/ember-data`\r\n- If you only get as far as making a list of commonly searched for links, that's ok! Go ahead and make a PR, and other contributors may help with doing the routing.\r\n\r\nHere is the landing page that exists today that covers only Ember.js:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1248\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2020-10-15 at 11 59 53 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16627268/96211547-99f28c80-0f42-11eb-85b5-4e5322f7fc50.png\">\r\n",
