    "active_lock_reason": null,
    "body": "**NOTICE** https://github.com/emberjs/ember-inspector is releasing v4.0.0 soon, so any that should be the baseline for this work, and not the currently published version (v3.13.2 on my Firefox browser).\r\n\r\nAt the moment, some of the screenshots in the Ember Inspector chapter of the guides are out of date. For example, the screenshots at https://guides.emberjs.com/v3.17.0/ember-inspector/component-tree/ still show the \"View Tree\" panel, which I believe has been removed for some time now. And, of course, https://guides.emberjs.com/v3.17.0/ember-inspector/view-tree/ should be removed.\r\n\r\nThe first phase of the work is to identify which screenshots are out of date so they can be replicated. For now I would not change the introduction page. Part of this work is also confirm which versions of ember.js make Ember Inspector show the \"View Tree\" or not, so we can backport the updated screenshots to the Guides for that version.\r\n\r\nOnce we have agreed on the work identified in the previous phase, we move to the second phase where we create issues to address said work.",
