    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "active_lock_reason": null,
    "body": "[qunit-dom](https://github.com/simplabs/qunit-dom) simplifies making assertions against the DOM, and has been included by default in new ember-cli applications for quite a while (introduced in [this RFC](https://emberjs.github.io/rfcs/0116-qunit-dom.html) and landed in ember-cli back in ember-cli@3.2.0).\r\n\r\nAn example of the difference between what we have now and what things would look like if we migrated an example from the \"Building a simple component\" page to qunit-dom is:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n  test('should toggle wide class on click', async function(assert) {\r\n    await render(hbs`<RentalListing @rental={{this.rental}} />`);\r\n    assert.notOk(this.element.querySelector('.image.wide'), 'initially rendered small');\r\n    await click('.image');\r\n    assert.ok(this.element.querySelector('.image.wide'), 'rendered wide after click');\r\n    await click('.image');\r\n    assert.notOk(this.element.querySelector('.image.wide'), 'rendered small after second click');\r\n  });\r\n```\r\n\r\nto:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n  test('should toggle wide class on click', async function(assert) {\r\n    await render(hbs`<RentalListing @rental={{this.rental}} />`);\r\n    assert.dom('.image.wide').doesNotExist('initially rendered small');\r\n    await click('.image');\r\n    assert.dom('.image.wide').exists('rendered wide after click');\r\n    await click('.image');\r\n    assert.dom('.image.wide').doesNotExist('rendered small after second click');\r\n  });\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Pages\r\n\r\n- [ ] Introduction\r\n- [ ] Test Types\r\n- [ ] Testing Application\r\n- [ ] Testing Basics\r\n- [ ] Testing Components\r\n- [ ] Testing Helpers\r\n- [ ] Testing Controllers\r\n- [ ] Testing Routes\r\n- [ ] Testing Models",
